                        <locus>Fol. 2a</locus>, contains Waqf and ownership stamps as well as a note by <persName type="supplied" key="person_f4385">Yusuf, son of Mika’il the Physician (al-Mutaṭabbib)</persName> that it came into his possession “one day [ <foreign xml:lang="ar">yawma’idhin</foreign> ]” in Aleppo in the year <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" notAfter="1337" notBefore="1337">1337</date> AH [ <date calendar="#Gregorian" notBefore="1918" notAfter="1918">1918 CE</date> ].</p>
